The '''Charbodians''' were the inhabitants of the [[Charbodia system/Legends|Charbodia system]] in the [[Inner Rim/Legends|Inner Rim]].<ref name="Atlas">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref><ref name="Planetnamia">{{JCFCite|url=posts/27848315|board=Literature|thread=The Essential Atlas and Galactic Cartography: Official Discussion|user=[[Jason Fry|jasonfry]]|date=2007-12-11|time=7:59 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170916153037/http://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-essential-atlas-and-galactic-cartography-official-discussion.21938930/page-43|quote=I wouldn't get your hopes up re alien homeworlds, beyond simple stuff like the Planetnamian species getting a Planetnamia on the map or things Dan and I can account for with a relatively quick reference.|archivefile=File:JasonFry-JCFAtlasHomeworlds.png}} [[Jason Fry]], co-author of ''[[The Essential Atlas]]'', stated his intention to create homeworlds for numerous species based on context implied from their names. Charbodia appears to be one such case.</ref> One Charbodian worthy of note was a [[Unidentified Charbodian cook|military cook]] at a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] medical station on [[Drongar/Legends|Drongar]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="MedStar I: Battle Surgeons">''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]'', Chapter 18.</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Charbodians are mentioned in the novel ''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]'', written by [[Michael Reaves]] and [[Steve Perry]] and published by [[Del Rey]] in [[2004]]. The book does not specify whether the term ''Charbodian'' refers to a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]] or is merely a [[Planet/Legends|planetary]] demonym, such as [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] or [[Hapan]].

